  <config>
    <documentation>
<![CDATA[The WT-100 Energy Thermostat

From the Properties page you can change the following parameters:
  Debug Mode:  
  Temperature Calibration:
  Heat Cutoff Point:
  Cool Cutoff Point:

From the Properties page you can view the following information:
  Version:  This is the version of the driver
  Firmware Version:  Current firmware on the WT-100
  MAC:  The MAC address of the WT-100
  Battery Level:  of the batteries in the WT-100

From the Properties page you can view the following WT-100 settings which can be changed by resetting the WT-100 (see below)
  HVAC Type:  Gas Furnace, Electric Furnace, or Heat Pump
  Auxiliary Stage type:  
  Emergency Stage type:   types 
  Reversing Valve:  O/B (Heat Pumps only) must be configured from the WT-100.  

To change any of these settings you must reset the WT-100 to the factory default settings and re-add the WT-100 to the project.  To reset the WT-100 to the factory default settings press the Mode/Off button 13 times, followed by the down button 4 times, followed by the Mode/Off button 13 times.  In the factory default state the WT-100 will display a “C” (Conventional Heat) or “HP”  (Heat Pump).  Refer to the Installation Guide for information about how to configure the WT-100 for your HVAC system.   
]]>
</documentation>
